Notes:
- v0.1.0 is the latest upstream release tag at pin time (checked via
  `git ls-remote --tags`). It resolves to the same commit as the tag ref.
- The previously vendored source in the old repo
  (3d-car-assembler/vendor/box3d-experiment/box3d-main.zip) was an
  unpinned `main`-branch snapshot with no recorded commit. This pin
  replaces that with an exact, reproducible commit.
- All box3d C API symbols used by native/bridge.c were checked against
  this pinned commit's include/box3d/*.h and are unchanged: b3CreateWorld,
  b3DestroyWorld, b3World_Step, b3CreateBody, b3DestroyBody, b3MakeBoxHull,
  b3CreateHullShape, b3CreateSphereShape, b3CreateCapsuleShape,
  b3Body_ApplyLinearImpulse, b3Body_SetLinearVelocity,
  b3Body_SetTargetTransform, b3CreateSphericalJoint, b3CreateRevoluteJoint,
  b3CreateDistanceJoint, b3World_Explode, b3World_CastRayClosest,
  b3Body_SetType, b3Body_GetLinearVelocity, b3Body_SetAwake,
  b3World_GetAwakeBodyCount, b3World_GetCounters, b3Body_GetPosition,
  b3Body_GetRotation, b3World_GetContactEvents, b3World_GetSensorEvents,
  plus the new-wrapper symbols b3DestroyJoint, b3Body_SetAngularVelocity,
  b3Body_GetAngularVelocity, b3Body_ApplyForce, b3Body_ApplyTorque,
  b3Body_SetTransform. No structural drift found; no bridge.c fixes
  were required for this pin.
- `b3CreateWorld` is `#define`d to `b3CreateWorldDoublePrecision` only
  when `BOX3D_DOUBLE_PRECISION` is defined at compile time. We do not
  define it, so the single-precision `b3CreateWorld` symbol is used,
  matching the existing (pre-extraction) app build.

